      <section id="about">
        <h1>About My Town News</h1>
        <p>My Town News is a free, independent weekly publication covering San Francisco's neighborhoods in depth. We publish every Friday, with a dedicated issue for each of the city's neighborhood clusters — from North Waterfront to Bayview & Excelsior.</p>
        <p>We are not affiliated with any city agency, advertiser, political organization, or real estate interest. Our only obligation is to the readers who live in these neighborhoods.</p>
      </section>

      <section id="standards">
        <h2>Editorial Standards</h2>

        <h2>How we research and write</h2>
        <p>Stories in My Town News are compiled from public sources, with assistance from AI. Our reporting process works as follows:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>We search and review public sources including city agency announcements, neighborhood association communications, established local media, library and cultural institution event calendars, and business websites.</li>
          <li>AI tools assist in researching, drafting, and organizing content from these sources.</li>
          <li>Every factual claim is traceable to a source listed on the Sources page of each issue.</li>
          <li>Readers should verify important details at the cited source before acting on them.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Quotes and attribution</h2>
        <p>We do not use invented or illustrative quotes. Statements attributed to individuals appear only when sourced to a verifiable public statement, press release, or published interview — with the source listed on the sources page. Named individuals appear only in their publicly documented roles. When the source is an organization or agency rather than a named individual, we attribute to the organization.</p>

        <h2>Images</h2>
        <p>We use photography from Unsplash, with photographer credit displayed on each image. Images are selected to match story content and geography.</p>

        <h2>Directory listings</h2>
        <p>Directory listings are assembled from public business listings, business websites, and the SF Chamber of Commerce. They are editorial-only; no business pays to appear in the directory. We refresh listings quarterly, or when stories surface new openings or closures.</p>

        <h2>Corrections</h2>
        <p>We correct errors promptly. If you spot an error, please <a href="mailto:{{ site.email }}">email us</a> or use the tip form below.</p>
      </section>

